                     <interp inst="def1-1062-18430227" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">RICHARD PECK</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18430227-1062-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18430227-1062-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="deception"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18430227-1062-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="fraud"></interp> for obtaining a loaf of bread by false pretences.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-1273" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-1273" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-1273" type="surname" value="BRANCH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-1273" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN BRANCH</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a baker, and live in St. James's-street, Islington. I do business with Mr. Ramsay. On the 3rd of Feb. the prisoner came and asked for a quartern loaf for Mr. Ramsay—my wife asked which Mr. Ramsay—he pointed to the house of Mr. Ramsay, which is at the corner, and said, "That"—I let him have the loaf on the faith of his coming from Mr. Ram<lb></lb>say—I watched him as far as the corner to see that it was correct, and as he turned, the corner I judged it was—he was soon after brought back by the officer.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-1274" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-1274" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-1274" type="surname" value="RAMSAY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-1274" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN RAMSAY</persName>
                  </hi>. My house is near Mr. Branch's shop—I did not autho<lb></lb>rize the prisoner to fetch a loaf for me on the 3rd of Feb.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-1275" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-1275" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-1275" type="surname" value="WITHERS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-1275" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS WITHERS</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable N</hi> 211.) I had seen the prisoner loitering about—I stopped him with the loaf—I asked where he got it—he said he bought it for 7<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—I took him to the prosecutor's shop—he then said a boy sent him for it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I was passing by, and a young man at Mr. Ramsay's asked me to go for a quartern loaf for Mr. Ramsay; I could not see the man again; I was going towards Mr. Ramsay's house with it. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> He had passed the house nearly ten yards.</p>
